-- Germany Joins Belgium, Switzerland in Qualifying for World Cup
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-11T20:40:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-11/germany-joins-belgium-switzerland-in-qualifying-for-world-cup.html
Germany, Belgium and Switzerland
claimed places in soccer’s 2014  World Cup  by winning their
European qualifying groups.  Germdany beat Ireland 3-0, Belgium defeated Croatia 2-1 and
Switzerland beat Albania 2-1. The trio joins Italy and the
Netherlands as European qualifiers for the World Cup in Brazil.  The winners of each of the nine groups in Europe advance to
the World Cup, with the eight best runners-up entering a playoff
for the continent’s final four places.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
